_:N895c6ea5846141958498f7f464180cfb <http://schema.org/name> "Zoe Sweet" .
_:Ne4de099c56cb4f57bdcd398fbfbc814e <http://schema.org/item> <https://www.gov.uk/> .
_:N895c6ea5846141958498f7f464180cfb <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Zoe joined the Cabinet Office in December 2025 as Director of Employee Experience and People Performance within the Government People Group. This is her first role in the Cabinet Office, where she leads the Inclusive Practice team, oversees initiatives to shape Civil Service culture and People Insights, and directs the future shape of the Civil Service people Strategy and Workforce function. </p>\n\n<p>Zoe has over 20 years’ experience across public and civil service, in Local Government transformation, devolved Government in Wales and latterly in UK Government at the Ministry of Justice. The focus of her work has been on system-wide effectiveness and transformation, with a particular interest in the challenges facing leaders in building resilient and agile organisations. </p>\n\n<p>Outside of her professional role, Zoe is a published contributing author. Most notably, ‘Developing Resilient Organizations (2014), and ‘Public Value – Purpose, Passion and Perseverance: creating public value through public sector leadership’ (Routledge, 2019). Most recently, Zoe has written about HR and OD approaches to culture in ‘Who Cares Wins: Leadership Practice for the 21st Century’ (Amazon, 2024).</p>\n" .
